title: For Sale:  Norinco SKS bullpup like Ak 47 ak47 rifle 7.62x39
postcontent:
This is a Norinco SKS (Chinese) rifle that shoots the 7.62x39 round. I originally purchased this rifle when it was put together on a different plastic stock. I purchased it for 400. I installed a bullpup stock that I bought just over 200 and added a buffer recoil pad (to reduce recoil). The barrel still has a lot of life left in it. Shoots very accurately and flawlessly.

The upgraded bullpup stock shortens the SKS about 5-6 inches from the previous length. I originally built this because I enjoy learning the different weapon platforms and I thought this would be a great shooter. Absolutely no surprises, this rifle shoots beautifully. The few times that I took it to the range, there is always a small audience behind me trying to figure out what I'm shooting. If you have friends or family that shoots, or you just want to show someone up that is different from what everyone else has, then this is the rifle for you. Or if you just like to have fun and blast away with inexpensive steel ammo, then this is also for you.

Replacement parts for the Norinco are cheap and are plentiful because of U.S. companies making compatible parts between all of the SKS platforms for all the different countries who manufacture it. The overall recoil is very manageable, if you wanted to take someone with a small frame to range they would have a blast without any concerns of injury.

I figured that whoever wants to buy it will have to pay for the transfer and background check fee. So I cut the price down from 800 to 700 help cover the cost of those transaction fees at whichever local gun shop we commit our transaction.

What is in this packaged deal?

1 Norinco SKS with a custom bullpup stock

800 rounds of ammunition (40 rounds of PDX1 Defender, 40 rounds of winchester white box brass, and the rest of the ammo is Tulammo steel cased)

5 20 round magazines
3 30 round magazines
2 40 round magazines
(all magazines are reliable)

20 stripper clips (for quick ammo loading)

1 steel ammo can with 7.62 markings.

NOTE: Magazines will be disassembled and provided to purchaser as parts kits, exactly how the gun shops in Colorado sell the magazines. This rifle is 922r compliant the entire stock kit is made in USA as well as the magazines and buffer pad that I installed.

title: For Sale:  AMT AutoMag III, 30 Carbine, 98%+ with Box, Paperwork, 6 Factory Mags
postcontent:
This is an exceptionally nice AMT AutoMag III semi-auto pistol that is chambered in the desirable and very collectible .30 Carbine rifle round.    

I'm the original owner and this pistol has had just less than three fifty round boxes of ammo fired through it since new. This will be the closet thing you'll find to NIB, and there are precious few AutoMag III's that are truly NIB.

It's the brainchild of the late Harry Sanford and is one of the more unusual and most sought after of all the pistols in the AutoMag line. The .30 Carbine chambering is quite unique and I'm not aware of any other semi-auto production pistol in this chambering.

Overall the pistol is 98%+ condition with the only wear coming from the 147 rounds that were fired through it. You'd have a tough time finding a nicer one for sure.

Pistol and magazines are made from high quality stainless steel and the grips are a black Lexan type material.    

Included is the original numbers matching box that's in great shape. Plus all of the factory literature that shipped with the pistol from the factory.    

Additionally 6 AMT factory original magazines are included and only one of them has ever had a round loaded in it. 

Finally there is 240 rounds of ammo included:  
(2) 50 round boxes Armscor FMJ 
(2) 50 round boxes of PPU SP  
(2) 20 round boxes Federal Classic 

If you look at GunBroker you'll see that an AutoMag III .30 Carbine in this condition with matching factory box and literature routinely bring $1200 and up with two mags. So my price with 6 mags (these are a bare minimum of $50 each) with the ammo is quite fair. Therefore lowball offers will not be entertained nor will they be responded to.

I'm asking $1500 for the package. However, if by chance you'd rather not have the ammo then I'm fine with keeping it as I have a M1 .30 Carbine rifle. So I'll subtract $125 for the ammo taking the price for the pistol, it's box and the 6 magazines to $1375.00

Pistol must be picked up in the Brandon area by a legal age Florida resident - No Shipping. A proper bill of sale will be provided.

Thanks for looking
